f8f6f4 instructions have different pseudos depending on the used formats.

In the disassembler table, we only have the variants with the largest register classes which assume using an fp8/bf8 format for both operands. The actual register class depends on the format in blgp and cbsz operands. Adjust the register classes depending on the used format.

### onSymbolStart() {#afec69108aa44466b2b0dfdd41a76aab1}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Expected&lt; bool &gt; AMDGPUDisassembler::onSymbolStart (<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/symbolinfoty">SymbolInfoTy</a> &amp; Symbol, uint64&#95;t &amp; Size, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/arrayref">ArrayRef</a>&lt; uint8&#95;t &gt; Bytes, uint64&#95;t Address) const</>}
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
Used to perform separate target specific disassembly for a particular symbol.

May parse any prelude that precedes instructions after the start of a symbol, or the entire symbol. This is used for example by <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/webassembly">WebAssembly</a> to decode preludes.

Base implementation returns false. So all targets by default decline to treat symbols separately.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="Symbol">- The symbol.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Size">- The number of bytes consumed.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Address">- The address, in the memory space of region, of the first byte of the symbol.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Bytes">- A reference to the actual bytes at the symbol location.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
- True if this symbol triggered some target specific disassembly for this symbol. Size must be set with the number of bytes consumed.
<ul>
<li><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> if this symbol triggered some target specific disassembly for this symbol, but an error was found with it. Size must be set with the number of bytes consumed.</li>
<li>False if the target doesn&#39;t want to handle the symbol separately. The value of Size is ignored in this case, and Err must not be set.</li>
</ul>
</SectionUser>

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/lib/target/amdgpu/disassembler/amdgpudisassembler-h/#l00169">169</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/lib/target/amdgpu/disassembler/amdgpudisassembler-h">AMDGPUDisassembler.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/lib/target/amdgpu/disassembler/amdgpudisassembler-cpp/#l02507">2507</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/lib/target/amdgpu/disassembler/amdgpudisassembler-cpp">AMDGPUDisassembler.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
